<subSubSection id="C36696BB8E5AFFB4FF1AFAAED837FD7F" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="143" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC3C5308E5AFFB4FF1AFAAED837FD7F" blockId="1.[163,1071,1365,1592]" lastBlockId="2.[163,1070,203,665]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="143" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">
Comment: This species, the 
<typeStatus id="54C77B928E5AFFB7FDBEFAADDB4EFA8D" box="[519,563,1366,1387]" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">type</typeStatus>
species of the subgeneric name 
<emphasis id="B90819228E5AFFB7FC36FAADDD53FA8D" box="[911,1070,1366,1387]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Phanerosphena</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E5AFFB7FF1AFA88D86BFA6F" author="PACE R" box="[163,278,1395,1417]" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" pagination="125 - 150" refId="ref7684" refString="PACE R. (1991): Aleocharinae dello Yemen (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona 15 (1988): 125 - 150." type="journal article" year="1991">PACE 1991</bibRefCitation>
, was previously known only from two localities in 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E5AFFB7FC97FA88DA0AFA6E" box="[814,887,1395,1416]" name="Yemen" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Yemen</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E5AFFB7FC3EFA88DA87FA6F" author="PACE R" box="[903,1018,1395,1417]" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" pagination="125 - 150" refId="ref7684" refString="PACE R. (1991): Aleocharinae dello Yemen (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona 15 (1988): 125 - 150." type="journal article" year="1991">PACE 1991</bibRefCitation>
) and originally described as 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E5AFFB7FE1AFA6BDA5FFA40" authorityName="Pace" authorityYear="1991" box="[419,802,1424,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rougemonti" subGenus="Phanerosphena">
<emphasis id="B90819228E5AFFB7FE1AFA6BD898FA43" box="[419,485,1424,1445]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Atheta</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B90819228E5AFFB7FE43FA6BDBE4FA43" box="[506,665,1424,1445]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Phanerosphena</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B90819228E5AFFB7FD17FA6ADA5FFA40" box="[686,802,1425,1446]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">rougemonti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. An examination of the above material, which represents the first record from 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E5AFFB7FD55FA56DA0AFA25" box="[748,887,1453,1475]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
, revealed that 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E5AFFB7FBA1FA55D86AFA06" authorityName="Pace" authorityYear="1991" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rougemonti">
<emphasis id="B90819228E5AFFB7FBA1FA55D86AFA06" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">A. rougemonti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a close relative of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E5AFFB7FE4EFA30DA23FA06" authority="(FAUVEL 1878)" baseAuthorityName="FAUVEL" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[503,862,1482,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pellucida">
<emphasis id="B90819228E5AFFB7FE4EFA30DBC6FA06" box="[503,699,1483,1504]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Acrotona pellucida</emphasis>
(FAUVEL 1878)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E5AFFB7FC2AFA30D82DFA18" authority="(BRUNDIN 1952)" baseAuthorityName="BRUNDIN" baseAuthorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oxypodoides">
<emphasis id="B90819228E5AFFB7FC2AFA30DD52FA06" box="[915,1071,1483,1504]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">A. oxypodoides</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E5AFFB7FF12FA13D834FA18" author="BRUNDIN L" box="[171,329,1512,1534]" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" pagination="93 - 145" refId="ref7387" refString="BRUNDIN L. (1952): Acrotona - Studien. (Gattung Atheta, Col., Staphylinidae). - Entomologisk Tidskrift 73: 93 - 145" type="journal article" year="1952">BRUNDIN 1952</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. In his revisionary work, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E5AFFB7FDE4FA13DA7AFA18" author="BRUNDIN L" box="[605,775,1512,1534]" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" pagination="93 - 145" refId="ref7387" refString="BRUNDIN L. (1952): Acrotona - Studien. (Gattung Atheta, Col., Staphylinidae). - Entomologisk Tidskrift 73: 93 - 145" type="journal article" year="1952">BRUNDIN (1952)</bibRefCitation>
attributed them to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E5AFFB7FC69FA13D83AF9FD" authority="THOMSON 1859" authorityName="THOMSON" authorityYear="1859" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90819228E5AFFB7FC69FA13DD53FA1B" box="[976,1070,1512,1533]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Acrotona</emphasis>
THOMSON 1859
</taxonomicName>
, which in those days was regarded as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E5AFFB7FCC5F9FED9A5F9DE" authority="THOMSON 1858" authorityName="THOMSON" authorityYear="1858" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90819228E5AFFB7FCC5F9FEDAC3F9FC" box="[892,958,1541,1562]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Atheta</emphasis>
THOMSON 1858
</taxonomicName>
, but today is treated as a distinct genus by most authors. Subsequently, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E5AFFB7FC0AF9D8DD53F9D1" baseAuthorityName="FAUVEL" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[947,1070,1570,1592]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pellucida">
<emphasis id="B90819228E5AFFB7FC0AF9D8DD53F9D1" box="[947,1070,1570,1592]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">A. pellucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FF6DFF37D809FF07" baseAuthorityName="BRUNDIN" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[212,372,204,225]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oxypodoides">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FF6DFF37D809FF07" box="[212,372,204,225]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">A. oxypodoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were assigned to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FD0DFF37DA84FF07" authority="BERNHAUER 1909" authorityName="BERNHAUER" authorityYear="1909" box="[692,1017,203,225]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Paradilacra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FD0DFF37DA4DFF07" box="[692,816,204,225]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Paradilacra</emphasis>
BERNHAUER 1909
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E59FFB4FF1AFF12D830FF19" author="SMETANA A" box="[163,333,233,255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" pagination="505 - 698" refId="ref7869" refString="SMETANA A. (2004): Staphylinidae, subfamilies Omaliinae - Dasycerinae, Phloeocharinae - Apaticinae, Piestinae - Staphylininae, pp. 237 - 272, 329 - 495, 505 - 698. - In: LOBL I. &amp; A. SMETANA (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. II. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphylinoidea. - Stenstrup, Apollo Books: 942 pp." type="book chapter" year="2004">SMETANA 2004</bibRefCitation>
) and then reinstated in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FDCEFF12DBA8FF18" authorityName="THOMSON" authorityYear="1859" box="[631,725,233,254]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FDCEFF12DBA8FF18" box="[631,725,233,254]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Acrotona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E59FFB4FCADFF12DAC4FF19" author="ASSING V" box="[788,953,233,255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" pagination="1105 - 1124" refId="ref7200" refString="ASSING V. (2010): Four new species and additional records of Staphylinidae from Spain, primarily from the south (Insecta: Coleoptera). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 42 (2): 1105 - 1124." type="journal article" year="2010">ASSING (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FC69FF12D86AFEFA" authorityName="Assing &amp; Schülke &amp; M.R &amp; A.S" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="PACE" baseAuthorityYear="1991" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rougemonti">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FC69FF12D86AFEFA" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Acrotona rougemonti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FE90FEFDD8D4FEFD" baseAuthorityName="FAUVEL" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[297,425,262,283]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pellucida">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FE90FEFDD8D4FEFD" box="[297,425,262,283]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">A. pellucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FE52FEFDDBF7FEFD" baseAuthorityName="BRUNDIN" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[491,650,262,283]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oxypodoides">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FE52FEFDDBF7FEFD" box="[491,650,262,283]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">A. oxypodoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FC69FEFDD991FEDF" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FC69FEFDDD53FEFD" box="[976,1070,262,283]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Acrotona</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
particularly by a different morphology of the median lobe of the aedeagus, of the parameres, and by longer and more slender legs, suggesting that both taxa form separate lineages. On the other hand, a close relationship is indicated by similar external characters and a similar morphology of the spermatheca. In consequence, until the systematic affiliations have been thoroughly studied based on a phylogenetic approach, 
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FF1AFE4DD83FFE2D" box="[163,322,438,459]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Phanerosphena</emphasis>
is proposed to represent a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FD6FFE4DDA49FE2D" authorityName="THOMSON" authorityYear="1859" box="[726,820,438,459]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FD6FFE4DDA49FE2D" box="[726,820,438,459]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Acrotona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Other species that have been attributed to 
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FEDBFE28DB7CFE0E" box="[354,513,467,488]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Phanerosphena</emphasis>
are: 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FD8EFE28DA30FE0F" authority="PACE 1986" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1986" box="[567,845,467,489]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perlaeta">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FD8EFE28DBABFE0E" box="[567,726,467,488]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Atheta perlaeta</emphasis>
PACE 1986
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FCCFFE28D9AAFDE0" authority="PACE 1988" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tronqueti">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FCCFFE28DA8FFE0F" box="[886,1010,467,489]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">A. tronqueti</emphasis>
PACE 1988
</taxonomicName>
) (Himalaya, 
<collectingRegion id="49B80BD28E59FFB4FEC9FE0BDB65FDE0" box="[368,536,496,518]" country="Saudi Arabia" name="Ash Sharqiyah" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Oriental region</collectingRegion>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FD8AFE0ADA22FDE0" authority="PACE 1998" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1998" box="[563,863,496,518]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="retroarmata">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FD8AFE0ADBA8FDE0" box="[563,725,497,518]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">A. retroarmata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E59FFB4FD5CFE0ADA22FDE0" author="PACE R" box="[741,863,496,518]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" pagination="911 - 982" refId="ref7757" refString="PACE R. (1998): Aleocharinae della China: parte IV (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Revue Suisse de Zoologie 105 (4): 911 - 982." type="journal article" year="1998">PACE 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E59FFB4FCCFFE0BDA81FDE0" box="[886,1020,496,518]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FBA1FE0AD8AAFDC5" authority="BERNHAUER 1915" authorityName="BERNHAUER" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alboguttata">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FBA1FE0AD865FDC5" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">A. alboguttata</emphasis>
BERNHAUER 1915
</taxonomicName>
(Afrotropical region), 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FD7CFDF5DA8EFDC5" authority="(KRAATZ, 1859)" baseAuthorityName="KRAATZ" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[709,1011,525,547]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentata">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FD7CFDF5DA3AFDC5" box="[709,839,526,547]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">A. tridentata</emphasis>
(KRAATZ, 1859)
</taxonomicName>
(Oriental region), 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FEF1FDD0DBE2FDA7" authority="CAMERON 1950" authorityName="CAMERON" authorityYear="1950" box="[328,671,555,577]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coprophila">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FEF1FDD0D89DFDA6" box="[328,480,555,576]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">A. coprophila</emphasis>
CAMERON 1950
</taxonomicName>
(Oriental region), and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FC01FDD0D815FDB8" authority="SCHEERPELTZ 1962" authorityName="SCHEERPELTZ" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FC01FDD0DD50FDA7" box="[952,1069,555,577]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">A. spinosa</emphasis>
SCHEERPELTZ 1962
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E59FFB4FECFFDB3D8CBFDB8" box="[374,438,584,606]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E59FFB4FE78FDB3DB5DFDB8" box="[449,544,584,606]" name="Thailand" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Thailand</collectingCountry>
). However, at least 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E59FFB4FD53FDB2DAFEFDB8" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1998" box="[746,899,585,606]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="retroarmata">
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FD53FDB2DAFEFDB8" box="[746,899,585,606]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">A. retroarmata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unlikely to be correctly assigned to 
<emphasis id="B90819228E59FFB4FE38FD9DDB5DFD9D" box="[385,544,614,635]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Phanerosphena</emphasis>
, as can be inferred from the illustrations provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E59FFB4FF7AFD78D83BFD7F" author="PACE R" box="[195,326,643,665]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" pagination="911 - 982" refId="ref7757" refString="PACE R. (1998): Aleocharinae della China: parte IV (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Revue Suisse de Zoologie 105 (4): 911 - 982." type="journal article" year="1998">PACE (1998)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
